EFS (Elastic File System) is a fully managed, shared network file system provided by AWS. 
Unlike EBS which attaches to one EC2 instance,
EFS can be mounted on hundreds of EC2 instances at the same time across multiple Availability Zones.

📌 Simple Analogy:
EBS Volume → Personal USB Stick 🖥️ (one person uses it)
EFS → Shared Network Drive 🌐 (everyone in the office accesses it)

Feature	              EFS	                          EBS	                    Instance Store
Type	                Shared Network File System	  Network Block Storage	  Physical Disk
Attachment	          Hundreds of EC2s ✅	          One EC2 at a time	      Fixed to one EC2
Availability Zone	    Multiple AZs ✅	              Single AZ only	        Single AZ only
Data Persistence	    ✅ Persistent	                ✅ Persistent	          ❌ Lost on stop
Cost	                Higher	                      Moderate	              Free with instance
Scaling	              Auto scales ✅	              Manual resize	          Fixed size
OS Support	          Linux only	                  Linux & Windows	        Linux & Windows
